\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 Serves 8 
\f0 \
\

\f1\fs44 2- 3 pound corned beef briskets\
6 large carrots, peeled & cut into large chunks\
3 large onions, peeled & quartered\
2 teaspoon dry mustard\
a few sprigs each of fresh parsley & fresh thyme, tied together\
4 small heads of cabbage\

\f0 \

\f1 Put the corned beef brisket into a large stock pot.\'a0 Add the carrots, onion, mustard & herb bundle.\'a0 Cover with cold water & bring to a boil.\'a0 Reduce the heat to a simmer, cover the pot & cook for 2 hours.\'a0 Trim the outer leaves of the cabbage off.\'a0 Cut into quarters & add to the pot.\'a0 Cook for an additional 2 hours.\
Remove the corned beef from the pot & transfer to a cutting board.\'a0 Remove any visible fat from the brisket & cut into thin slices against the grain.\'a0 Using a slotted spoon, remove the cabbage & carrots.\'a0 Transfer the corned beef & vegetables to a serving platter & serve.\
This meal is particularly great when served with some {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.theparsleythief.com/2010/03/guinness-mustard-horseradish-cream.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 Guinness Mustard & Horseradish Cream}} as condiments.\cell \lastrow\row
